class OrderBook(object):
    def __init__(self, ob_data):
        '''This class represents an order book at any point in time.  The time stamp of the orderbok is saved as an instance property'''
        data_list = []
        for ii in ob_data[1].items():
            data_list.append((ii[0],ii[1][0], ii[1][1]))

        df = pd.DataFrame.from_records(data_list, columns=["P","Q","S"])
        self.timestamp = ob_data[0]
        df = df.sort_values(by=["P"])

        # Now make the orderbook cumulative.
        #Bid side first
        df_bids = df[df['S'] == "B"]

        df_bids = df_bids.sort_values(by="P", ascending=False)
        # Note that when y is negative, the buy side of the orderbook will be used (since liq. demanders want to sell)
        df_bids['tot_y'] = -df_bids['Q'].cumsum()
        #print(df_bids)

        # Now ask side
        df_asks = df[df['S'] == 'S']
        df_asks = df_asks.sort_values(by="P", ascending=True)

        df_asks['tot_y'] = df_asks['Q'].cumsum()
        self.df = pd.concat([df_bids, df_asks], axis=0)

        self.df['y'] = self.df['tot_y']
        self.df = self.df.drop('tot_y', axis=1)

        self.percentile = 0.99

    def get_range(self):
        '''Finds a reasonable range of prices for estimating the orderbook'''
        bb = self.df[self.df['S']=='B']['P'].max()
        ba = self.df[self.df['S']=='S']['P'].min()
        midpoint = (bb + ba)/2
        bid_cutoff = -self.df[self.df['S']=='B']['y'].min()*self.percentile
        ask_cutoff = self.df[self.df['S']=='S']['y'].max()*self.percentile
        #print(-bid_cutoff, ask_cutoff)
        bids = self.df[(self.df['S']=='B') & (self.df['y'] > -bid_cutoff)]
        asks = self.df[(self.df['S']=='S') & (self.df['y'] < ask_cutoff)]
        df_temp = pd.concat([bids, asks])
        df_temp = df_temp.sort_values('P')
        lower = df_temp['P'].min()
        upper = df_temp['P'].max()
        return (lower, upper)

    def get_bbo(self):
        '''Returns the best bid and best offer in a tuple (best_bid, best_offer)'''
        bb = self.df[self.df['S']=='B']['P'].max()
        ba = self.df[self.df['S']=='S']['P'].min()
        return (bb, ba)

    def get_midpoint(self):
        '''Returns the midpoint of the best bid and best offer'''
        bb = self.df[self.df['S']=='B']['P'].max()
        ba = self.df[self.df['S']=='S']['P'].min()
        mp = (bb + ba)/2
        return mp

    def estimate_ols(self, lower, upper):
        '''Estimate the slope of the orderbook using prices between lower and upper.'''
        df = self.df[(self.df['P'] >= lower) & (self.df['P'] <= upper)]
        df = df.sort_values(["P"])
        model = sm.ols(formula='y ~ P', data=df).fit()
        #print(model.summary())
        return model


    def parameter_estimates(self, lower, upper):
        '''Estimates the parameters p_{0}, and 2\sigma_{u}/\sqrt{\Sigma_{0}} using OLS'''
        est = self.estimate_ols(lower,upper)
        #pprint(est.params)
        p_0 = -est.params['Intercept']/est.params['P']
        #pprint(p_0)
        noise_to_signal = 0.5*est.params['P']
        return {'p': p_0, 'ratio': noise_to_signal}



    def plot(self, lower, upper):
        '''Plot the orderbook between prices lower and upper.'''
        df = self.df[(self.df['P'] >= lower) & (self.df['P'] <= upper)]
        df = df.sort_values(["P"])
        plt.plot(df['P'], df['y'])
        plt.show()
        plt.close()

    def plot_estimates(self, lower, upper):
        '''Plots the orderbook between lower and upper as well as the estimates of the orderbook'''
        df = self.df[(self.df['P'] >= lower) & (self.df['P'] <= upper)]
        df = df.sort_values(["P"])
        plt.plot(df['P'], df['y'])
        params = self.estimate_ols(lower, upper)
        pvec = np.linspace(lower, upper, 100)
        yvec = [ params.params['Intercept'] + params.params['P']*ii for ii in pvec ]
        plt.plot(pvec, yvec)
        plt.show()
        plt.close()

class OrderBookSet(object):

    def __init__(self, ob_list):
        self.ob_list = [ OrderBook(ob) for ob in ob_list ]


    def plot_noise_ratio(self, title):
        '''Plots the noise ratio over time for each OrderBook in the OrderBookSet'''
        ts = []
        rat = []
        for ob in self.ob_list:
            ts.append(ob.timestamp)
            ra = ob.get_range()
            rat.append(ob.parameter_estimates(*ra)['ratio'])

        plt.plot(ts, rat)
        plt.xlabel("Seconds since midnight")
        plt.ylabel("$\sigma_{u}/\sqrt{\Sigma_{0}}$")
        plt.title(title)
        plt.show()
        plt.close()

    def price_slope_correlation(self):
        '''Returns the between the midpoint of the price and the slope of the orderbook'''
        mp = []
        rat = []
        for ob in self.ob_list:
            ra = ob.get_range()
            rat.append(ob.parameter_estimates(*ra)['ratio'])
            mp.append(ob.get_midpoint())

        mpa = np.array(mp)
        rata = np.array(rat)
        return np.corrcoef(mpa, rata)

    def get_noise_ratio(self):
        '''Returns the noise ratio for each orderbook as a timeseries of the form (timestamps, noise_ratios)'''
        ts = []
        rat = []
        for ob in self.ob_list:
            ts.append(ob.timestamp)
            ra = ob.get_range()
            rat.append(ob.parameter_estimates(*ra)['ratio'])

        return (ts, rat)

    def get_imputed_p0(self):
        '''Returns the imputed p0 as a timeseries of the form (timestamps, imputed_p0s)'''
        ts = []
        p0 = []
        for ob in self.ob_list:
            ts.append(ob.timestamp)
            ra = ob.get_range()
            params  = ob.parameter_estimates(*ra)
            #pprint(params)
            gamma = params['p']
            beta = params['ratio']
            i_p0 = -gamma/beta
            p0.append(i_p0)

        return (ts, p0)

    def get_p0(self):
        '''Returns the midpoint of the BBO as a timeseries of the form (timestamps, p0)'''
        ts = []
        p0 = []
        for ob in self.ob_list:
            ts.append(ob.timestamp)
            p0.append(ob.get_midpoint())

        return (ts, p0)
